name: ThromboembolicDisease
title: Thromboembolic Disease
description: SNOMED CT intensional (rule-based) value set for defining thromboembolic disease diagnoses, available for a range of potential uses including problem-oriented views of relevant clinical information, clinical decision support rules, electronic patient registries, and data analytics.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Broad grouper of diagnosis concepts for thromboembolic disease.),(Data Element Scope: Employs SNOMED CT concept hierarchies primarily in the Disorder (Clinical finding) branch, though some can be in the Situation with Explicit Context branch or the Procedure branch.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes deep vein and visceral venous and arterial thromboses, and history of the same.),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes superficial venous thrombosis as well as vascular thromboses in the brain, eye, heart, skin and capillaries.)
